    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1862-05-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1862-05-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="589" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d589">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Corwin</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                                Seward</persName>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 24.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of the United States of
                                        America,</hi>
                            <hi rend="italic">Mexico,</hi>
                        </placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1862-05-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">May</hi> 20, 1862.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir:</hi> I have the honor to acknowledge the
                            receipt of your despatches Nos, 43, 44, and 45, with the two treaties
                            between the United States and Mexico lately ratified at Washington. The
                            ratifications will be exchanged to-morrow, and the next day Mr. Plumb,
                            with Captain Shufeldt, will leave for Vera Cruz.</p>
                <p rend="center">* * * * * * * * *</p>
                <p>Very respectfully, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>THOMAS CORWIN.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>Hon. <hi rend="smallcaps">William H. Seward</hi>, <hi rend="italic">Secretary of State of the United States, Washington, D.
                                C.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
